particular attention to the small city of Kamloops, BC, this collection explores the impact of extended, short term, and unique leadership collaborations. It addresses local responses to homelessness, sustainability, food security, and more. It offers insight into the role of the university in the small city as a place of learning, and a contributor to positive change. Based on active engagement, this book reveals the barriers present in addressing local needs, and the transformations that can be achieved through effective collaboration. It offers valuable insights into flexible practices that respond to the needs of community organizations and recognizes the challenges associated with resource constraints and capacity limitations. This unique collection provides new insights into the twists and turns of leadership and learning in the small city.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aClinical medicine -- Periodicals. 0aClinical psychology -- Periodicals. 0aCommunity leadershipzBritish ColumbiazKamloops. 0aCommunity leadershipzBritish Columbia. 0aLibros electronicos. 0aLocal governmentzBritish ColumbiazKamloops. 0aMedicina clínica -- Publicaciones periódicas. 0aPsicología clínica -- Publicaciones periódicas. 0aQuality of lifezBritish Columbia. 0aSocial participationzBritish Columbia. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh  aBC.  aBritish Columbia.  aCanada.  aKamloops.  aadult learners.  acommunity engaged research.  acommunity history.  acommunity leadership.  acommunity learning.  acommunity partnerships.  acommunity-engaged research.  acommunity-engaged.  aequality of life.  ahomelessness initiatives.  ahomelessness.  aknowledge support.  aleadership and learning.  aleadership.  alearning.  aoral history.  aorgani